## Coordination with other tasks

- **T11 Executor (Tue/Wed/Fri 16:30)** — reads BACKLOG `Awaiting professional input` section and SKIPS those pages until recording arrives
- **T10 Strategist (daily 20:09)** — when scoring refresh actions, gives +10 bonus to pages where a recording has arrived (professional content waiting to ship)
- **T12 Learner (Sun 18:05)** — tracks: % of briefs that produced a recording; which page types lifted most after professional input shipped; flags reviewers who haven't responded in 21d
- **T15 Mixpanel (Wed 10:00)** — provides freshest conversion data for the "high impression / low conversion" scoring signal
- **Verifier** — when an eventual refresh action incorporates a transcribed quote, Verifier Check 5 (quality bars) confirms the quote is attributed and that consent flag matches the page treatment

---

## First-run note

This is the inaugural setup. For the first week:

1. Read frontmatter from `src/content/illnesses/*.mdx` and `src/content/treatments/*.mdx` to build the reviewer mapping. Save to `brain/memory/reviewer-mapping.md` for future reuse.
2. If no `brain/memory/professional-input-history.md` exists, create empty file.
3. If no `briefs/professional-input/` folder exists, create it.
4. Run the full scoring + selection. Even if the data is sparse for some signals (CTR baseline, competitor video gap), produce 6 picks using whatever signals are available — note `LIMITED_BASELINE: true` in log.
5. Post Slack with brief summary + flag any reviewers missing from the mapping.

## Excluded topics list

Create `brain/memory/excluded-topics.md` if it doesn't exist, seed with:

```
# Topics professionals should NOT be asked to opine on
# Auto-disqualifies pages mentioning these as primary topic

- pricing, cost, fee
- company / about us
- app technical features
- referral programs
- testimonials (these have a separate workflow)
- emergency / acute crisis (handled by Suicide & Safety gate)
```

This list is editable by Kushal anytime; Meta-Learner can propose additions if it spots discomfort patterns.
